@{b}MIN()@{ub}

Usage:@{b}MIN(number,number[,number,...])@{ub}

Returns the minimum of the supplied arguments, all of which must be numeric. At
least two parameters must be supplied.

Example:
@{fg shine}
        say min(2.1,3,-1)               ==>-1
